{"name": "rhei", "metadata": {"name": "rhei", "version": "0.5.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython"], "home_page": "https://github.com/dkrystki/rhei", "license": "Apache 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Package that implements simple stopwatch class.", "upload_time": 1564320589}, "documentation": ["# Rhei - Simple stopwatch class\n\n```{image} https://badge.fury.io/py/rhei.svg\n:target: https://pypi.org/project/rhei/\n```\n\n```{image} https://circleci.com/gh/dkrystki/rhei.svg?style=svg\n:target: https://circleci.com/gh/dkrystki/rhei\n```\n\n```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/dkrystki/rhei/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n:target: https://codecov.io/gh/dkrystki/rhei\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.6-blue.svg\n:target: https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-360/\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.7-blue.svg\n:target: https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-370/\n```\n\nRhei is a Python 3 package that implements simple stopwatch functionality including pausing, resetting and reverse counting.\n\n## Installation\n\n```console\npip install rhei\n```\n\n## In a nutshell\n\n```python\nfrom time import sleep\nfrom rhei import Stopwatch\n\nstopwatch = Stopwatch()\nstopwatch.start()\nsleep(5)\nstopwatch.value  # 5.0\n\nstopwatch.pause()\nsleep(2)\nstopwatch.value  # 5.0\n\nstopwatch.reset()\nstopwatch.value  # 0.0\n\nstopwatch.reset(10.0)\nstopwatch.value  # 10.0\nstopwatch.start(reversed=True)  # Start counting down\n\nsleep(2)\nstopwatch.value  # -2.0\n```\n\n## Development\n\nRhei uses docker to create an isolated development environment so your system is not being polluted.\n\n### Requirements\n\nIn order to run local development you have to have Docker and Docker Compose installed.\n\n### Starting things up\n\n```console\ndocker-compose up -d\n```\n\n### Logging into the docker terminal\n\n```console\n./bin/host/terminal\n```\n\nThe code is synchronised between a docker container and the host using volumes so any changes ( `pipenv install` etc ) will be affected on the host.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "rhei", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "rhei.Stopwatch", "xref": {"fqname": "rhei.stopwatch.Stopwatch", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType", "bases": ["Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType.INIT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType.START", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType.PAUSE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType.REVERSE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType.STOP", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.EventType.RESET", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.Event", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "rhei.stopwatch.Event.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stopwatch", "type": {"name": "Stopwatch", "xref": {"fqname": "Stopwatch", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "time_value", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rhei.stopwatch.Event.finish", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "retu